# Server JavaScript

CommonJS (`require` / `module.exports`). Node 16.x. No TypeScript on server.

## Formatting (Prettier)

- Double quotes, semicolons, trailing commas, 120 char width, 2-space indent
- Before finishing, run in the API container: `ctl exec api npm run lint` and `ctl exec api npm run prettier` (see project overview for full `ctl` usage)

## Config and env

Use `config` package — never read `process.env` outside `server/src/config/`:

```javascript
const config = require("config");
if (config.get("features.juicy.enabled")) { /* … */ }
```

## Logging

Use Winston helper — include structured context objects:

```javascript
const logger = require("../helpers/logger");
logger.warn(`[${server.name}] Unable to fetch: ${error.message}`, { server, error });
```

## Conventions

- Albion API field names stay PascalCase (`EventId`, `GuildName`) — match upstream API
- Mongo `_id` → `id` string conversion happens in `ports/database.js`; services use `id`
- i18n for bot user strings via `helpers/locale` (`t("KEY")`), not hardcoded English in commands
- Unused args prefixed with `_` or named `req`/`res` to satisfy ESLint
